Từ điển Anh - Việt
◘['sti:mə]
*danh từ
 ■tàu chạy bằng hơi nước
 ■chõ, nồi hấp, nồi đun hơi

Anh - Anh
steamer
■ noun
1》 a ship or boat powered by steam.
2》 a type of saucepan in which food can be steamed.
3》 a device used to direct a jet of hot steam on to a garment in order to remove creases.
4》 informal a wetsuit.

Kết hợp từ & Cấu trúc câu
steamer
n. an oceangoing; tramp steamer

sentences.en: Please see your way to catch the first available steamer.

sentences.vi: Có một tàu bánh guồng trong hồ Windermere.

sentences.en: The shriek of the machine's steamer pierced her ears.

sentences.en: As there is no direct steamer from our port to your port it is imperative for you to delete the clause "by direct steamer", from your L/C.

sentences.en: There will be a direct steamer for London in the middle of next month.
sentences.vi: Sẽ có tàu đi suốt đến Luân Đôn vào giữa tháng sau.

sentences.en: We will try but cannot engage to ship the goods on the steamer mentioned.
